June 24, 2014
2014 Financial Advisor Retirement Symposium 


Jon Sabes heads GWG Holdings, Inc., a specialty finance firm he co-founded in 2006. As the CEO of GWG Holdings, he oversees the strategic development of the company’s financial service offerings and its debt offering product development. Jon Sabes recently attended Financial Advisor’s Retirement Symposium, where he spoke on the continuing development of the secondary market for life insurance and the unique opportunities retirees have to participate in this newly emerging marketplace.  The editors of Financial Advisor Magazine and Private Wealth Magazine partnered in hosting the Fifth Annual Retirement Symposium in Las Vegas, Nevada. The event took place from April 29th through April 30th at Caesars Palace and included speeches from industry experts and a forum for discussion of topics relevant to individual retirement needs. The conference was well attended by financial advisors seeking innovative product solutions and ideas for retirees - the fastest growing population demographic in the United States.The Retirement Symposium also offered several educational sessions that qualified as CE credit toward the CFP Board and CIMA designations. These included Retirement: The View From 30,000 Feet Up moderated by Evan Simonoff, Equity-Income Investing for Retirement moderated by Jeff Schlegel, and Finding Hidden Assets For Retirement moderated by Jason Plucinak of GWG Life.                            


